Pre-Game Insights: Moldova have scored two or more goals in five of their last 10 home matches.
Malta have lost eight of their last 10 away games and failed to score in five of those.
Ion Nicolaescu has scored 10 goals in his last 20 international appearances.
Erling Haaland is an excellent bet to score, given his nine goals this season and incredible Champions League record. Inter’s defensive vulnerabilities make it likely he’ll extend his scoring streak.
Post-Match Reflections: Moldova’s home advantage, coupled with Malta’s poor form, makes a home win the most likely outcome.
With Moldova’s key players performing well and Malta struggling for goals, a comfortable victory for the hosts is on the cards.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Stadionul Zimbru is the venue for the match.
The match is scheduled for September 7, 2024, at 5pm UK time.
